A former street boy in Eldoret town’s dreams of joining a public secondary school of his choice after excelling in last year’s KCPE examination have come true. Sixteen-year-old Mnangat Nelson, who scored 371 marks, was included on the list of 16 needy students from Uasin Gishu county to benefit from Equity Bank’s sponsorship programme. Mnangat moved the crowd during the ceremony to unveil the beneficiaries held in Eldoret town. He narrated how he spent sleepless nights and went hungry on the strees for 11 years. Mnangat was registered at Natimerir Primary School in Lodwar. He aspires to become a doctor